article.headline: Northwestern St. 31, Stephen F.Austin 12
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. (AP) -- Byron Lawrence ran for 231 yards and a touchdown as Northwestern State beat winless Stephen F. Austin, 31-12, Saturday night. The Demons (4-7, 3-4 Southland Conference) never trailed. They had the only first-quarter touchdowns, on runs of 9 yards by Dudley Guice and 10 yards by Sterli Endsley. Lawrence's 31-yard run made it 21-0 before the Lumberjacks (0-11, 0-7) got their first touchdown on a 52-yard pass by Jeremy Moses to Aaron Rhea, for a 21-7 halftime score. Less than a minute into the second half, Guice caught a 72-yard touchdown pass from Drew Branch, who made all four of his passes for a team-leading 95 yards. Jeremy Claybon made SFA's second score on a 13-yard run. Robert Weeks, who also made all of NSU's extra-point kicks, completed the scoring with a 40-yard field goal. Moses, 10-for-21 with one interception, passed for 138 yards. He was sacked three times. Jabar Williams led SFA's rushers with 85 yards on 19 carries. Ryan Gooch had punted six times for 257 yards, the longest of them 80 yards. Lawrence's total made him No. 5 on Northwestern State's all-time rushing list for a single game and No. 4 for a season, with 1,377 yards.
